# LFC VBS 2026 "Deliverance" -- Print-Ready PDF Generator

## Sub-Agent Delegation Protocol

Opus handles planning, contract writing, and synthesis. Sub-agents handle execution.
Full protocol — three-tier decision, contract template, model selection, parallel rules — lives in the
`/agent-orchestration` global skill.

## What This Is

A Python-based generator that produces print-ready PDF worksheets for Little Farms Chapel's 2026 Vacation Bible School. The theme is "Deliverance" covering Exodus (Slavery, Plagues, Passover/Red Sea). It outputs a master PDF and per-level PDFs for all 4 levels across 3 days.

## How to Run

```bash
python3 generate.py
```
Outputs go to `output/`. Takes ~30 seconds. Requires `weasyprint` and `jinja2`.

## Project Structure

```
generate.py          -- Main script: assembles HTML pages and renders PDFs via WeasyPrint
wordsearch.py        -- Puzzle generators: word search, crossword, word scramble
fetch_coloring_pages.py -- One-time script to download coloring page images (legacy, see below)
data/content.json    -- All curriculum content: days, scriptures, activities, words, clues
templates/base.html  -- Single HTML/CSS template (all styles inline, WeasyPrint-compatible)
assets/coloring/     -- Coloring page images (PNG/JPG), AI-generated via Nano Banana
assets/svg/          -- SVG artwork (not all used currently)
assets/cache/        -- Intermediate processed images from legacy fetch script
output/              -- Generated HTML + PDFs
```

## Architecture

### Levels & Days

- **Level 1** (Ages 3-K): Drawing + Coloring pages. Each day shows "Introduce" scripture reference and a Key Concept on the drawing page.
- **Level 2** (Elementary): Drawing + Coloring pages. Same "Introduce" + Key Concept format as Level 1 (shared key concepts).
- **Level 3** (Older Elementary): Worksheet + Puzzle pages (word search day 1, crossword day 2, scramble day 3) + answer keys. Has its own deeper key concepts.
- **Level 4** (Youth/Adult): Worksheet + Discussion + Puzzle pages (same puzzle types as L3 but harder words) + answer keys. Shares L3's key concepts plus has discussion questions.

### Key Concepts

- **Levels 1-2** share the same key concepts (simple summaries of each day's passage).
- **Levels 3-4** share the same key concepts (deeper theological concepts).
- L1-2 key concepts appear on the drawing page. L3-4 key concepts appear on the worksheet page.

### Page Generation Flow

`generate.py:generate_all()` iterates levels/days, calls page-maker functions that return HTML strings. All pages are concatenated into a single HTML document, then `base.html`'s `{{ content }}` placeholder is replaced and rendered to PDF.

### Puzzle Generation (`wordsearch.py`)

- `generate_wordsearch()` -- Grid-based word search with 8 directions, random fill
- `generate_crossword()` -- Criss-cross puzzle. Greedy placement: tries all remaining words at each step, picks best fit (most intersections, most compact). Proper adjacency checking rejects parallel neighbors. Runs up to 500 attempts keeping best result.
- `generate_scramble()` -- Word scramble with secret message (circled letters spell a phrase). Uses `_match_words_to_secret()` to reorder words via greedy most-constrained-first matching so each secret-message letter maps to a word that actually contains it.

### Content Data (`data/content.json`)

Structure: `levels[] > days[] > activities{}`. Day-level fields:
- `reading`: "Introduce ..." (L1-2) or "Read ..." (L3-4)
- `key_concept`: single string (used on days with one concept)
- `key_concepts`: array of strings (used on days with multiple concepts)
- `catechism_qa`: array of {q_num, question, answer} (L3-4 only)
- `discussion_questions`: array of strings (L4 only)

Activity types:
- `wordsearch`: `{prompt, words[]}`
- `crossword`: `{prompt, words[], clues{}}` -- clues maps WORD -> hint string
- `scramble`: `{prompt, words[], secret_message}`
- `drawing/coloring`: `{prompt, instruction}`
- `list`: `{prompt}`

### CSS / Styling

All CSS lives in `templates/base.html`. WeasyPrint-compatible (no flexbox/grid for layout -- uses `display: table/table-cell` instead). Color scheme: deep red (#8B1A1A), gold (#C5961A), parchment tones. Letter-size pages with 0.5in/0.65in margins.

Two drawing area sizes: `.drawing-area` (7in, full page) and `.drawing-area-short` (5.2in, used when key concept is shown above).

Page numbers are rendered in the bottom-right corner via WeasyPrint's `@page @bottom-right` margin box, matching the footer text style. The title page is excluded using `@page :first`.

## Key Design Decisions

- Crossword puzzle pages show **clue hints** (from the `clues` dict) in the Across/Down lists, plus a **word bank** below. Answer keys show the actual **words** in the Across/Down lists.
- Crossword generator uses greedy best-fit (not random shuffle) with strict adjacency rules: non-intersection cells reject any parallel neighbors, and cells before/after words must be empty.
- Word search pages have no answer key (by design). Crossword and scramble pages do.
- The `make_puzzle_page()` dispatcher selects puzzle type by day number: day 1 = word search, day 2 = crossword, day 3 = scramble.

## Coloring Page Images

Located in `assets/coloring/`. AI-generated via Nano Banana for consistent quality and age-appropriate content. Mapped to (level, day) pairs via `IMG_MAP_COLORING` dict in `generate.py`:

| Key | Filename | Subject |
|-----|----------|---------|
| (1,1) | moses_staff | Moses holding his staff |
| (1,2) | nile_blood | The Nile turning to blood |
| (1,3) | red_sea_parting | The Red Sea parting |
| (2,1) | moses_pharaoh | Moses confronting Pharaoh |
| (2,2) | hail_egypt | The ten plagues of Egypt (composite scene) |
| (2,3) | red_sea_crossing | Israelites crossing the Red Sea (front-facing perspective, pillar of fire behind) |

Only levels 1-2 have coloring pages. If an image file is missing, a dashed-border placeholder SVG is rendered instead. Images can be PNG or JPG (any extension is auto-detected).

## Extending

- To add a new day or level: add entries to `data/content.json`, then add page-building logic in `_build_level_pages()` if needed.
- To add a new puzzle type: implement generator in `wordsearch.py`, add page renderer in `generate.py`, add dispatch in `make_puzzle_page()`.
- To change styling: edit `templates/base.html` CSS. Remember WeasyPrint limitations (no CSS grid, limited flexbox).
- To replace coloring images: drop new files in `assets/coloring/` with matching filenames (any image extension works).
